'''Digestible Indispensable Amino Acid Score''' ('''DIAAS''') is a [[protein quality]] method, proposed in March 2013 by the [[Food and Agriculture Organization ]] to replace the current protein ranking standard, the [[Protein Digestibility Corrected Amino Acid Score]] (PDCAAS).<ref>[http://www.ift.org/food-technology/daily-news/2013/march/07/fao-proposes-new-protein-quality-measurement.aspx FAO proposes new protein quality measurement. March 2013]
